    title: "Full Stack Software Engineer",
    description:
      "\u003cp\u003eThe Why:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOur vibrant engineering team of 12 is looking to hire driven, curious developers with 0 - 3 years of experience to help cultivate our stack at a proven (8 years in) tech company in downtown Minneapolis.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAs consumers, we have plenty of ways to talk online about the service we have received but we don’t have the same friction-free ways to engage in-the-moment with real people at the businesses we visit. Kipsu provides a new way for businesses and guests to engage through real-time digital channels, transforming what it feels like to give and receive great service.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe How:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe love the work we do and how we do it. We have deliberately built an engineering team that is tight-knit, non-dogmatically agile and embraces talented individuals who want to make a difference. We are on the lookout for a Software Engineer who shares our passion and is ready to take on the exciting and complex challenges of a rapidly growing software company. Read on if this sounds like the type of culture you would excel in!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe What:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAs an engineer on our small, congenial team, you’ll have the chance to:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHave input, make an impact, and release code nearly every day\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDesign and build innovative new product features, enhancements, subsystems, and microservices with zero-downtime deployments, adding to our rapidly evolving codebase\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFind new frameworks, tools, technologies, and practices, and put them to work to solve interesting problems (we embrace pragmatic microservices design patterns that allow us to pick the right tools/languages for the job)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTake responsibility, make architectural choices, and generally be empowered to drive meaningful changes\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eJoin our blameless retros as we learn from our mistakes (as individuals and as a team) with a focus on experimentation and continuous improvement\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCollaborate with a motivated team of peers on software design and code review to ensure that the team is always putting out the best product (and code) possible\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWork with individuals outside of engineering to develop new products and features that help our clients effortlessly communicate with their guests\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Who:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe’re hiring engineers who:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAre proficient in full stack development and have experience writing scalable object-oriented code; we will consider candidates with 0 - 3 years of experience (those with less than a year of professional experience will submit a code sample - see bottom of posting for instructions).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUnderstand how to break down complex problems into manageable pieces that can be continuously deployed to production\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWant to work together as part of a high energy, high achieving team\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHave an entrepreneurial streak or a history of working on side projects\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWant to contribute to and lead projects in areas like real-time communication, data analysis, microservices, user experience, API and SDK development, cloud infrastructure and beyond\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBonus points for experience:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWorking in a solid, scalable backend codebase by applying object-oriented principles using PHP, Node.js, Java, Go, or other languages and frameworks\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBuilding web applications with Javascript, and bringing in knowledge from working with modern frameworks like Angular, Vue, Backbone, Knockout, or React\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUtilizing Amazon Web Services (AWS) or other cloud computing platforms\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBuilding native mobile applications for iOS or Android\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWorking in the customer service domain and on customer service software​\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe know we’re not one of the large tech companies (not yet, anyway), but we like it that way. Our engineering team can fit around a table at lunch and stay in easy, regular communication. We score a 10 on the Joel Test and are working towards getting that to a 12.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn addition to the opportunity to be a key part of a small, focused team at a successful and rapidly growing startup, we offer competitive salary and benefits, stock options, and the trust and freedom to move the proverbial needle. If you’re looking to hone your skills and learn a whole host of new ones as a valued member of our high-performing team, then we’d like to meet you.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eConnect:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTo apply please submit your resume and in your cover letter, please answer the following questions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTell us about a time when you were bold in how you solved a technical problem.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHow has your past work set you up to excel as a Full Stack Engineer at Kipsu? We want to hear all about the amazing things you've built, your successes and your failures. \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIf you are in the first year of your career as a software engineer, please also share a sample of your code from one recent solo project that you are proud of in particular.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe'd like to see:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eA personal project, if possible - if that isn't possible, we'll gladly accept a school or boot camp solo project (and the project can be complete or partially done)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eClean code that makes use of sound software engineering principles \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePlease provide context such as:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAnything in this project that particularly grabbed your interest or excited you\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAny personal touch you added, where you maybe went above and beyond (if for school), or an example of how you solved a particularly complex problem\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYour plans for proceeding if the project is partially done\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHow to run the project\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOne last thing– At Kipsu, we believe that our values, success, and future as a leader in our industry require a vibrant and diverse workforce. This is one of the many challenges we seek to solve, and we are intentional and active in recruiting talent that comes from all walks of life and building an environment that is inclusive to all backgrounds. We need your contribution to our team. Please, consider rolling up your sleeves and joining us on our journey.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe look forward to hearing from you!\u003c/p\u003e\n",
