    description:
      "\u003cp\u003eSympo®, Inc., with an office in San Dimas, CA , is an award-winning Quick Base® Solution Provider. Our Quick Base® Developer team provides businesses, across all industry categories, solutions to problems they didn’t even know they had! Our solutions are flexible, scalable, cost-effective and leverage web-based tools.\nSympo® is a growing and dynamic company, and we pride ourselves on our service, experience, knowledge, ethics and enthusiasm. Our mission and philosophy are quite simple: become our client’s trusted advisor, provide unparalleled services and serve our clients with integrity.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe currently have an opening on our Development Team for a Software Programmer in our San Dimas office. This position will provide advanced software programming capabilities coupled with Quick Base® application development and integration with other business systems. Solutions for our clients that are customized to meet their specific business needs.\nWe are looking for Software Programmers with experience and knowledge with programming languages such as (combination of any of the following) Python, JavaScript, jQuery, Ruby on Rails, PHP and HTML5 is required. This position will also be tasked with developing scripts, interacting with API’s and building web forms. And a demonstrable proficiency of exemplary level of organization and productivity.  This position will require attention to detail, the ability to work unsupervised effectively and efficiently, lead client-facing project activities that include analyzing client business needs, design and build custom database applications in Quick Base®.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSOFTWARE PROGRAMMER REQUIRED EXPERIENCE\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience as a Python Developer to interact with RESTful web services, push and pull data from various systems via Python’s requests and other supporting libraries\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUtilization of prebuilt classes and/or SDKs to enhance build speed and consistency. Add enhancements as necessary to reusable internal libraries and classes\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience with Django-based web application development and configuration to run under Apache on a Unix OS-based system. OR, Similar experience with a modern web application framework (e.g. Ruby on Rails) and a desire to learn a new framework.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBuild Django views to display HTML based templates that render and accept data in various formats. (E.g. calendars, input forms, PDF Documents)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience in UNIX Server management and set-up for web applications (e.g. install and configure Apache including CSR generation and SSL certificate installation)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSchedule scripts via cron utility and proficiency working via SSH and SFTP\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHTML AND JavaScript Development, create layouts, display data in styled format using HTML and CSS3. Experience with best practices for performance, responsive design, and cross-browser compatibility/limitations.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience contributing to and maintaining repositories in a version control system (e.g. Github or Subversion)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDESIRABLE EXPERIENCE AS A SOFTWARE PROGRAMMER COUPLED WITH QUICK BASE®\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eConsulting Background\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExpertise in building Apps in Quick Base® using the Quick Base® Application Development Platform\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLeadership in technical design and business process requirements including a combination of functionality and technical vision between usability, performance and budget options\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCommunication and leadership skills\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProject management and ability to drive software technology best practices\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou must have demonstrable experience working as a Software Programmer; self-motivated, self-managed and accountable.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUpon employment, the successful candidate will need to present evidence of their U.S. Citizenship or their legal right to live and work in the U.S.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSympo®, Inc. works as a team. Each and every individual here is key to our success! We enjoy a comfortable office environment that is professional, entrepreneurial, friendly, and supportive. We constantly strive to better our knowledge and performance, for the benefit of ourselves and our clients. We offer competitive compensation (based on experience) and benefits. If you are an experienced Software Programmer and if this is the environment you are looking for, send your resume and tell us why you should be our next Software Development Team Member.\u003c/p\u003e\n",
