    description:
      "\u003cp\u003eCompany description\nAt Red Hat, we connect an innovative community of customers, partners, and contributors to deliver an open source stack of trusted, high-performing solutions. We offer cloud, Linux, middleware, storage, and  technologies, together with award-winning global customer support, consulting, and implementation services. Red Hat is a rapidly growing company supporting more than 90% of Fortune 500 companies.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eJob summary\nThe Red Hat Engineering team is looking for a Principal Software Engineer to join us in Westford, MA to work on the KubeVirt project. In this role, you will design and implement  solutions for containers and virtual machines (VMs), contributing to industry-leading technologies like , Red Hat , libvirt, and . As a part of a geographically distributed team you will collaborate with multiple Red Hat engineering teams and open source communities around the globe. You’ll need to be motivated and curious with a passion for problem solving, Linux technologies, and open source.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePrimary job responsibilities\nPlay an active role in  and -related projects and communities, such as KubeVirt, , Red Hat , libvirt, and\nCreate and guide new feature development; contribute to open source projects in  and\nIntegrate changes in multiple projects and services into a consumable feature\nSubmit patches for bug fixes to the community and review patches from other members\nWork with the Quality Engineering (QE) team to ensure projects are tested correctly\nPublicize the team's work through blogs, web postings, or conference talks\nRequired skills\nBachelor's degree in computer science or equivalent work experience\nInterest in the  ecosystem (, Red Hat ) and\nExperience in storage and storage protocols, including NFS, iSCSI, etc.\n5+ years of experience in a Linux environment working with either , , , or C or C++\nExperience in Linux system programming\nMulti-threaded programming and management of shared resources synchronization in complex environments\nMotivated with the ability to quickly learn new technologies\nGood written and verbal communication skills in English\nFamiliarity with , clusters, and -related technologies like , Red Hat , -based Virtual Machine (), and Red Hat OpenStack Platform is a plus\nOpen source development experience is a plus\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRed Hat is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and an affirmative action employer. We review applications for employment without regard to their race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, ancestry, citizenship, age, veteran status, genetic information, physical or mental disability, medical condition, marital status, or any other basis prohibited by law.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRed Hat does not seek or accept unsolicited resumes or CVs from recruitment agencies. We are not responsible for, and will not pay, any fees, commissions, or any other payment related to unsolicited resumes or CVs except as required in a written contract between Red Hat and the recruitment agency or party requesting payment of a fee.\u003c/p\u003e\n",
